    "updated_at": "2016-08-13T20:42:22Z",
    "body": "with the buffer we get a crash, but with a string we get the cert and everything works. I've had problems with node::Buffer every time I've tried to use it and the only way I've ever successfully sent unmunged binary data is with something like this\n\n```\nconst uint8_t* data = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(body.c_str());\n  v8::String::NewFromOneByte(isolate(),\n      data, v8::NewStringType::kNormal, body.length()).ToLocalChecked();\n```\n"
